0East%20Coast%20because%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20in%20a%20place%20with%20lots%20of%20diversity.%20Moving%20to%20Boston%20was%20one%20step%20toward%20broadening%20my%20worldview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228fa250ca-6505-43b6-b333-6859bb895607%5C%22%3ESuccess%20meant%20climbing%20the%20corporate%20ladder%20to%20the%20top%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20college%2C%20I%20started%20working%20as%20an%20assistant%20account%20executive%20in%201992%20in%20Chicago%20at%20a%20huge%20global%20advertising%20agency%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ddb.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDDB%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20followed%20in%20my%20dad's%20footsteps%20as%20a%20marketer.%20He%20worked%20on%20many%20cool%20brands.%20I%20watched%20him%20work%20his%20way%20up%20in%20his%20career%20to%20become%20the%20CEO%20of%20Hagen%20Dazs%20eventually.%20He%20made%20the%20script%20of%20success%20clear%3A%20climb%20every%20rung%20of%20the%20corporate%20ladder%2C%20work%20for%20sexy%20brands%2C%20and%20get%20bigger%20and%20bigger%20titles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20rebellious%20growing%20up%2C%20but%20now%20I%20can%20see%20that%20his%20career%20path%20influenced%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2026%2C%20I%20was%20successful%20in%20my%20career%20and%20had%20an%20active%20social%20life.%20I'd%20even%20taken%20a%20four-month%20sabbatical%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Bsoulbbatical%26quot%3B%20as%20I%20call%20them%20now%2C%20to%20travel%20Europe.%20In%20my%20journals%20from%201996%2C%20I%20talked%20about%20following%20the%20winds%20of%20my%20soul%20and%20the%20tensions%20I%20felt%20in%20my%20career%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20know%20who%20to%20talk%20to%20about%20my%20doubts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20solution%20was%20to%20move%20to%20Istanbul%20for%20an%20international%20role%20at%20the%20agency%20I%20was%20working%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%2C%20I%20took%20this%20role%20because%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%20something%20different%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20know%20how%20to%20process%20that%20desire%2C%20so%20I%20stuffed%20it%20back%20down.%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20achieve%20a%20corporate%20career%20and%20travel%20%E2%80%94%20to%20reach%C2%A0success%20the%20Shelley%20Paxton%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20returned%20to%20the%20United%20States%20in%202000%20to%20take%20a%20senior%20role%20at%20AOL.%20I%20then%20continued%20to%20work%20in%20marketing%20roles%20with%20large%20clients%20like%20Visa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22766c9992-904c-4db0-bb1f-c065ac2bb3fb%5C%22%3EI%20wanted%20to%20rebrand%20myself%20after%20a%20divorce%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Harley%20Davidson%20hired%20me%20as%20VP%20of%20Global%20Integrated%20Marketing%20and%20Planning%20in%202010%2C%20I%20was%2040%20and%20had%20just%20gone%20through%20a%20very%20traumatic%20divorce.%20I%20felt%20like%20my%20life%20was%20upside%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarley%20Davidson%20was%20my%20first%20opportunity%20to%20work%20on%20the%20client%20side%20of%20marketing%2C%20not%20the%20agency%20side.%20I%20saw%20myself%20as%20a%20biker%20babe%20marketer%20for%20one%20of%20the%20most%20iconic%20motorcycle%20brands%20on%20the%20planet.%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BHell%20yes%2C%20I%20want%20to%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%20the%20role%20would%20be%20my%20chance%20for%20reinvention%2C%20but%20ultimately%2C%20it%20was%20my%20final%20lesson%20and%20wake-up%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22744e880b-56bd-49ea-aa2f-33016d744ceb%5C%22%3EIf%20I%20wasn't%20working%2C%20who%20would%20want%20me%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20struggled%20throughout%20my%20career%20with%20prioritizing%20work%20over%20my%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20an%20unfortunate%20pattern%20for%20me.%20Back%20in%202006%2C%20I%20agreed%20to%20go%20to%20Shanghai%20for%20a%20work%20assignment%20for%20Omnicom%20Media%20Group.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20my%20now%20ex-husband%20and%20I%20were%20trying%20to%20have%20children%20and%20wanted%20stability.%20Instead%20of%20honoring%20that%2C%20I%20said%20yes%20to%20the%20assignment