0Celsius%20and%20Chennai%20registered%20a%20temperature%20of%2039%20degrees%20Celsius.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20metropolitan%20cities%20usually%20register%20higher%20temperatures%20in%20May%2C%20June%20and%20July.%20This%20phenomenon%20is%20attributed%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwhat-is-the-urban-heat-island-effect-thats-making-metro-cities-hotter-5563318%5C%22%3Eurban%20heat-island%20effect%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20making%20the%20cities%20significantly%20warmer%20than%20their%20surroundings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FABSe5jFmbuA%3Fsi%3DNVcinkfazqZm3c9c%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20is%20the%20Urban%20Heat%20Island%20Effect%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20simple%20words%2C%20the%20urban%20heat%20island%20effect%20takes%20place%20when%20urban%20regions%20record%20higher%20temperatures%20than%20their%20rural%20surroundings.%20This%20mostly%20occurs%20due%20to%20human%20activities%2C%20buildings%2C%20and%20infrastructure%20in%20urban%20areas%20that%20absorb%20and%20retain%20heat%20more%20effectively%20than%20natural%20landscapes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20worth%20noting%20that%20rising%20temperatures%20are%20not%20limited%20to%20India%2C%20and%20the%20conditions%20are%20getting%20worse%20all%20over%20the%20world.%20According%20to%20scientists%2C%20one%20reason%20for%20this%20excessive%20heat%20in%20India%20is%20the%20El%20Nino%20effect%2C%20which%20is%20responsible%20for%20the%20change%20in%20the%20global%20weather%20pattern.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20is%20the%20El%20Nino%20Effect%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEl%20Ni%C3%B1o%20is%20characterised%20by%20unusually%20warm%20ocean%20temperatures%20in%20parts%20of%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean.%20It%20also%20results%20in%20the%20rise%20of%20sea%20surface%20temperatures.%20The%20El%20Nino%20cycle%20started%20in%202023%20and%20its%20effect%20is%20expected%20to%20last%20until%20June%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20phenomenon%20is%20responsible%20for%20the%20extreme%20summer%20this%20year.%20However%2C%20soon%20El%20Nino%20will%20start%20to%20weaken%20and%20La%20Nina%20will%20come%20into%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20is%20the%20La%20Nina%20Effect%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELa%20Nina%20is%20the%20cooling%20of%20the%20water%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean.%20While%20it%20occurs%20at%20irregular%20intervals%2C%20La%20Ninna%20is%20associated%20with%20widespread%20changes%20in%20the%20weather%20patterns.%20India%20is%20likely%20to%20witness%20a%20good%20monsoon%20this%20year%20once%20the%20La%20Nina%20comes%20into%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhy%20does%20heatwave%20occur%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20changes%20taking%20place%20in%20our%20atmosphere%20and%20oceans%20give%20rise%20to%20heatwave%20in%20the%C2%A0North%20Central%20and%20Eastern%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%20It's%20highly%20dangerous%20because%20it%20triggers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fehs.research.uiowa.edu%2Foccupational%2Fheat-stress%5C%22%3Eheat%20stress%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20our%20bodies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDry%20Heat%20Stress%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3EDry%20heat%20stress%20occurs%20when%20the%20temperatures%20rise%20but%20if%20the%20humidity%20remains%20low.%20In%20this%20intense%20heat%2C%20it%20becomes%20difficult%20for%20the%20body%20to%20cool%20down%20its%20temperature%20through%20sweating.%20This%20can%20lead%20to%20dehydration%20and%20other%20health-related%20concerns.%20There%20is%20less%20possibility%20of%20humidity%20in%20summer%20in%20Central%20and%20North%20Western%20India%2C%20therefore%2C%20the%20region%20faces%20a%20greater%20number%20of%20dry%20heat%20stress%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EMoist%20Heat%20Stress%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3EThis%20is%20humid%20heat%20stress.%20This%20occurs%20when%20the%20humidity%20gets%20mixed%20with%20rising%20temperature.%20In%20this%20condition%2C%20too%2C%20the%20body%20fails%20to%20cool%20down%20itself%20through%20sweating%20and%20heat%20stress%20rises.%20People%20in%20eastern%20coastal%20areas%20like%20Odisha%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20Maharashtra%20face%20such%20conditions.%20These%20regions%20record%20a%20high%20number%20of%20moist%20heat%20stress%20cases%20when%20the%20temperature%20is%20high%20in%20the%20monsoon%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20study%20by%20IMD%20revealed%20that%20in%20the%20last%2040%20years%2C%20in%20India%20(between%201980%20to%202020)%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%2030%25%20rise%20in%20heat%20stress%20cases%20due%20to%20humidity%20being%20involved%20with%20rising%20temperatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20this%20period%2C%20the%20average%20heat%20index%20in%20Central%20India%2C%20North%20West%20India%20and%20Eastern%20coastal%20areas%20witnessed%20their%20temperature%20rising%204%20to%205%20degrees%20Celsius%20above%20their%20normal%20summer%20temperature.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717063260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fd0p53lag_heatwave-afp_625x300_30_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhy-temperatures-in-indian-cities-are-rising-like-never-before-5778285%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22We%20are%20not%20even%20into%20June%20yet%2C%20and%20a%20large%20part%20of%20North%20and%20Central%20India%20is%20already%20grappling%20with%20severe%20heatwave.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhy-temperatures-in-indian-cities-are-rising-like-never-before-5778285%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mortgage%20Interest%20Rates%20Today%2C%20May%2030%2C%202024%20%7C%20Rates%20Inch%20Up%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%