_blank%5C%22%3Eequiring%20college%20degrees%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20toss%20another%20possible%20explanation%20into%20the%20mix%3A%20the%20unemployment-insurance%20system.%20The%20way%20firings%20are%20handled%20might%20actually%20affect%20whether%20guys%20get%20hired%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20some%20basics.%20When%20a%20worker%20is%20laid%20off%20or%20fired%2C%20they're%20generally%20eligible%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-file-for-unemployment-benefits-2020-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunemployment%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20program%20designed%20to%20help%20people%20stay%20afloat%20financially%20while%20they%20look%20for%20their%20next%20gig.%20After%20applying%20and%20being%20approved%2C%20which%20can%20be%20a%20pain%2C%20unemployed%20workers%20collect%20a%20check%20each%20week.%20The%20checks%20don't%20replace%20all%20their%20wages%3B%20the%20amount%20is%20generally%20less%20than%20half%20of%20what%20they%20were%20making%20before.%20It's%20something%20to%20tide%20them%20over%20so%20they%20can%20pay%20their%20bills%2C%20keep%20food%20on%20the%20table%2C%20etc.%2C%20and%20that's%20good%20for%20the%20economy%20because%20it's%20a%20drag%20on%20everything%20when%20people%20suddenly%20can't%20do%20those%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20straightforward%20enough%20idea%2C%20but%20the%20way%20we%20pay%20for%20UI%20is%20pretty%20wonky.%20Every%20business%20pays%20a%20tax%20into%20the%20pool%20of%20money%20that%20goes%20to%20paying%20unemployment%20insurance%3B%20the%20tax%20bill%20is%20footed%20by%20the%20employer%2C%20not%20the%20employee%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fis-social-security-taxable%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunlike%20Social%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20gets%20paid%20for%20by%20both.%20(Employers%20pay%20a%20certain%20percentage%20into%20UI%20on%20every%20paycheck%2C%20and%20those%20with%20more%20employees%20wind%20up%20kicking%20more%20in.%20It's%20sort%20of%20like%20the%20employer's%20part%20of%20Social%20Security.)%20But%20instead%20of%20it%20being%20a%20flat%20tax%20(the%20business%20kicks%20in%20X%20percentage%20each%20month)%20the%20rate%20can%20go%20up%20through%20a%20system%20called%20%26quot%3Bexperience%20rating.%26quot%3B%20The%20experience%20in%20question%20is%20how%20much%20the%20employer%20has%20laid%20off%20workers%20in%20the%20past%3A%20More%20layoffs%20mean%20a%20higher%20tax%20rate.%20The%20thinking%20is%20that%20the%20more%20workers%20the%20company%20has%20let%20go%2C%20the%20more%20it's%20pushed%20people%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funemployment-benefits-being-taxed-as-income-creates-new-woes-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edraw%20on%20the%20UI%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20therefore%20it%20should%20pay%20more%20in%20unemployment%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20behind%20this%20is%20understandable%20(though%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnext-recession-forecast-unemployment-insurance-has-many-problems-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecountries%20don't%20do%20UI%20this%20way%3C%2Fa%3E).%20If%20you%20want%20to%20discourage%20businesses%20from%20firing%20people%20willy-nilly%2C%20you%20penalize%20those%20that%20do.%20But%20in%20practice%20it's%20had%20some%20unintended%20consequences.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faibm.org%2Fpolicy%2Ffix-unemployment-insurance-to-help-young-men-into-work%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Matt%20Darling%2C%20a%20senior%20employment-policy%20analyst%20at%20the%20Niskanen%20Center%2C%20a%20center-right%20think%20tank%2C%20argues%20that%20the%20experience-rating%20system%20has%20made%20some%20employers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2304.05605%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereluctant%20to%20hire%3C%2Fa%3E%20workers%20they're%20worried%20won't%20work%20out%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20that%20young%20men%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20are%20the%20ones%20being%20harmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20going%20to%20get%20taxed%20for%20any%20employees%20that%20get%20laid%20off%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20more%20hesitant%20about%20hiring%2C%26quot%3B%20Darling%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt%20isn't%20the%20sole%20driver%2C%20but%20I%20think%20it's%20an%20important%20one.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20experience-rating%20system%20wasn't%20nationwide%20until%20the%20federal%20government%20in%20the%20mid-1980s%20mandated%20that%20states%20adopt%20the%20program.%20Darling%20looked%20at%20what%20happened%20when%20it%20was%20forced%20on%20the%20state%20of%20Washington%2C%20which%20held%20out%20on%20implementing%20the%20program%20until%201985.%20He%20compared%20it%20with%20Oregon%2C%20which%20already%20had%20an%20experience%20rating%20in%20place.%20The%20states'%20unemployment%20rates%20for%20young%2C%20entry-level%20workers%20moved%20in%20sync%20before%20Washington's%20experience%20rating%20was%20in%20place.%20When%20it%20was%20implemented%2C%20workers%20in%20Washington%20started%20to%20see%20higher%20unemployment.%20Darling%20found%20that%20after%20the%20experience%20rating%20was%20introduced%20in%20Washington%2C%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20for%20workers%2015%20to%2025%20%E2%80%94%20basically%20entry-level%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20increased%20by%202.5%20percentage%20points.%20The%20effect%20was%20driven%20almost%20entirely%20by%20young%20men%3A%20Unemployment%20went%20up%20by%202.7%20percentage%20points%20for%20young%20men%20but%20by%20only%200.1%20percentage%20points%20for%20young%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20does%20sort%20of%20tie%20into%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20that%20people%20have%20been%20thinking%20about%2C%26quot%3B%20Darling%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhy%20is%20the%20male%20employment%20rate%20declining%20in%20general%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20prospect%20of%20higher%20unemployment%20taxes%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.niskanencenter.org%2Fcreating-a-more-dynamic-unemployment-insurance-system-the-case-for-eliminating-experience-rating%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprompt%20employers%20to%3C%2Fa%3E%20steer%20clear%20of%20people%20they%20perceive%20as%20riskier%20workers%20or%20opt%20to%20hire%20contractors.%20In%20more-nefarious%20situations%2C%20they%20might%20try%20to%20discourage%20workers%20from%20applying%20for%20unemployment%20or%20make%20their%20employees%20so%20miserable%20that%20they%20quit%20and%20therefore%20aren't%20eligible%20for%20UI%20benefits.%20So%20why%20would%20young%20men%20bear%20the%20brunt%20of%20this%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22breakout-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fot6eE%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Employment-population%20ratio%2C%20men%20aged%2025-54%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22442%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EMen%20tend%20to%20outnumber%20women%20in%20economically%20vulnerable%20industries%2C%20such%20as%20manufacturing%20and%20construction.%20In%20recessions%2C%20those%20sectors%20are%20often%20hardest%20hit%2C%20meaning%20their%20jobs%20are%20among%20the%20first%20to%20go.%20(The%20pandemic%20recession%20was%20the%20exception.)%20Businesses%20in%20those%20sectors%20may%20also%20be%20extra%20sensitive%20to%20their%20experience%20ratings%3B%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20add%20even%20more%20to%20their%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20might%20also%20see%20young%20men%20as%20riskier%20to%20bring%20on%20board.%20Fairly%20or%20unfairly%2C%20there's%20a%20stereotype%20that%20young%20men%20are%20more%20volatile%2C%20more%20immature%2C%20and%20less%20responsible%20than%20their%20female%20counterparts.%20Darling%20notes%20that%20men%20drop%20out%20of%20college%20at%20higher%20rates%20than%20women%20and%20argues%20that%20the%20same%20behavioral%20differences%20that%20drive%20that%20trend%20could%20also%20mean%20businesses%20see%20them%20as%20a%20higher%20layoff%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheres-whats-next-for-unemployment-insurance-in-the-us-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20ideas%20out%20there%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funemployment-benefits-system-broken-pandemic-congress-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epolicy%20solutions%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcovid-era-unemployment-benefits-cuts-will-lower-us-incomes-by-145-billion-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efix%20the%20experience%20rating%20and%20UI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Darling's%20preference%20is%20to%20ax%20the%20experience%20rating%20and%20just%20pick%20a%20simple%20tax%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImplementing%20any%20of%20these%20solutions%20would%20be%20complicated%2C%20as%20there's%20rarely%20much%20political%20will%20to%20act%20on%20unemployment%20insurance.%20People%20realize%20how%20screwed%20up%20the%20system%20is%20when%20times%20are%20bad%20(see%3A%20the%20Great%20Recession%2C%20the%20pandemic)%2C%20but%20once%20things%20get%20back%20to%20normal%2C%20everyone%20sort%20of%20forgets.%20Whatever%20appetite%20for%20action%20there%20might%20have%20been%20in%20Congress%20dies%20out%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20no%20real%20constituency%20of%20people%20who%20consider%20themselves%20the%20%26quot%3Bunemployed%20worker.%26quot%3B%20Lawmakers%20on%20Capitol%20Hill%20and%20in%20state%20legislatures%20do%20not%20love%20talking%20about%20taxes%20unless%20they're%20cutting%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20why%20so%20many%20young%20men%20aren't%20working%2C%20it's%20a%20doozy.%20There's%20no%20quick%20fix%20for%20recessions%20or%20incarceration%20rates%20or%20pay%20or%20any%20of%20the%20many%20other%20factors%20driving%20the%20shift.%20But%20maybe%20a%20step%20in%20the%20right%20direction%20here%20is%20to%20at%20least%20talk%20about%20it.%20And%2C%20hey%2C%20if%20you're%20a%20business%20owner%2C%20maybe%20take%20a%20risk%20on%20that%20young%20guy%20who%20walks%20through%20your%20door%20instead%20of%20worrying%20about%20what%20it%20might%20cost%20you%20if%20you%20decide%20to%20fire%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployment-young-men-labor-force-jobs-unemployment-insurance-hiring-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717062782000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66576a031cd3b17790414294%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployment-young-men-labor-force-jobs-unemployment-insurance-hiring-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22America's%20young%20men%20have%20stopped%20working.%20One%20reason%20for%20the%20rise%20in%20joblessness%3A%20our%20broken%20unemployment%20system%20is%20stopping%20them%20from%20getting%20hired.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployment-young-men-labor-force-jobs-unemployment-insurance-hiring-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22HC%20dismisses%20plea%20to%20disqualify%20PM%20Modi%20from%20contesting%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717062501000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-110562100%2Cimgsize-661643.cms%22%2C%2