data-driven%20newsletter%2C%20has%20found%20that%20the%20most%20underslept%20people%20live%20in%20low-income%2C%20rural%20areas%2C%20primarily%20in%20the%20South.%20Residents%20of%20West%20Virginia%2C%20Kentucky%2C%20and%20Alabama%20regularly%20get%20the%20least%20amount%20of%20sleep%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20not%20because%20they%20don't%20have%20horsehair%20mattresses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20have%20found%20that%20stress%20is%20one%20of%20the%20strongest%20indicators%20of%20poor%20sleep.%20Economic%20stress%2C%20in%20particular%3A%20Americans%20in%20poverty%20report%20getting%20the%20least%20amount%20of%20sleep.%20In%20a%202022%20survey%2C%2087%25%20of%20Americans%20polled%20said%20they%20lost%20sleep%20worrying%20about%20their%20finances.%20And%20in%20a%202020%20study%2C%2013%25%20of%20newly%20unemployed%20people%20said%20they%20got%20four%20hours%20of%20sleep%20or%20less%20a%20night%2C%20half%20of%20what%20the%20average%20employed%20person%20gets.%20In%20counties%20where%20about%20half%20the%20population%20doesn't%20get%20enough%20sleep%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20in%20Alabama%2C%20unemployment%20rates%20are%20twice%20as%20high%20as%20the%20US%20average%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fupper-middle-lower-class-income-wealth-poverty-new-york-census-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emedian%20household%20incomes%3C%2Fa%3E%20hover%20around%20%2435%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22breakout-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FwnpCx%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Where%20people%20get%20the%20worst%20sleep%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22505%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EMingo%20County%2C%20tucked%20in%20the%20southwestern%20corner%20of%20West%20Virginia%2C%20is%20the%20most%20sleep-deprived%20county%20in%20the%20most%20sleep-deprived%20state.%20One-quarter%20of%20Mingo%20residents%20live%20in%20poverty%20%E2%80%94%20double%20the%20national%20average.%20On%20top%20of%20that%2C%20the%20county%20struggles%20with%20poor%20health%2C%20another%20major%20contributor%20to%20poor%20sleep.%20Nearly%20half%20of%20Mingo%20residents%20are%20obese%20(10%20percentage%20points%20higher%20than%20the%20national%20average)%20and%20one%20in%20three%20smoke%20cigarettes%20(triple%20the%20national%20average).%20Mingo%20is%20also%20home%20to%20the%20highest%20rates%20of%20hypertension%20and%20heart%20disease%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20end%20of%20the%20spectrum%20is%20Boulder%20County%2C%20Colorado%2C%20which%20you%20might%20call%20the%20sleep%20capital%20of%20America%3B%2080%25%20of%20residents%20reported%20being%20well%20rested.%20Here%2C%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20is%20one%20of%20the%20lowest%20in%20the%20state%2C%20and%20the%20median%20household%20income%20falls%20at%20%2492%2C000.%20It's%20also%20one%20of%20the%20healthiest%20counties%20in%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20major%20cities%20such%20as%20Manhattan%20and%20San%20Francisco%2C%20where%20the%20median%20incomes%20are%20%2490%2C000%20and%20%24126%2C000%20respectively%2C%20seven%20in%2010%20people%20reported%20getting%20sufficient%20sleep.%20Money%20may%20not%20buy%20happiness%2C%20but%20it%20does%20seem%20to%20buy%20better%20sleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMental%20and%20physical%20health%2C%20which%20tend%20to%20be%20worse%20in%20lower-income%20areas%2C%20also%20contribute%20to%20sleep%20inequality.%20In%20our%20analysis%2C%20we%20overlaid%20the%20CDC's%20sleep%20data%20with%20a%20CDC%20survey%20on%20mental%20health%20and%20found%20a%2079%25%20correlation%20between%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgood-sleep-routine-avoid-burnout-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emental-health%20problems%20and%20poor%20sleep%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%202022%20study%20by%20Columbia%20researchers%20found%20a%20similar%20relationship.%20According%20to%20Johns%20Hopkins%2C%20three-quarters%20of%20people%20with%20depression%20say%20they%20struggle%20to%20fall%20asleep%20or%20stay%20asleep.%20Other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC10267346%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20found%20that%20half%20of%20people%20with%20chronic%20pain%20and%20as%20many%20as%20half%20of%20people%20with%20cancer%20don't%20get%20enough%20sleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FO7cNW%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Places%20with%20worse%20sleep%20also%20face%20mental%20health%20challenges%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22436%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20factors%20build%20on%20each%20other.%20Economic%20stress%2C%20depression%2C%20and%20physical%20pain%20make%20it%20harder%20to%20sleep%2C%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20sleep%20makes%20all%20these%20situations%20more%20difficult%20to%20manage.%20Americans%20with%20sleep%20disorders%20earn%20an%20average%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC9340609%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%242%2C500%20less%3C%2Fa%3E%20each%20year%20than%20their%20well-rested%20peers%20and%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F390797%2Fpoor-sleep-linked-billion-lost-productivity.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20likely%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20have%20to%20leave%20their%20jobs.%20Researchers%20at%20Johns%20Hopkins%20University%20found%20that%20poor%20sleep%20increased%20the%20likelihood%20of%20developing%20the%20very%20diseases%20that%20keep%20people%20awake%20at%20night%20in%20the%20first%20place%3A%20cancer%2C%20dementia%2C%20heart%20disease%2C%20type%202%20diabetes%2C%20and%20obesity.%20It%20also%20accelerates%20the%20spread%20of%20certain%20cancers.%20Once%20these%20negative%20feedback%20loops%20begin%2C%20it%20can%20make%20it%20harder%20for%20people%20to%20dig%20out%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomic-inequality-costs-trillions-racial-gap-wealth-hiring-brookings-institution-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecycles%20of%20inequality%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20fix%20their%20sleep%20problems%2C%20people%20often%20resort%20to%20outlandish%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsleep-hacks-to-optimize-business-performance-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esleep%20hacks%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20using%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsolidcore-founder-anne-mahlum-shares-her-longevity-routine-weightlifting-cold-plunge-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ered%20light%20bulb%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20their%20bedroom%20or%20taking%20a%20cold%20shower%20before%20bed.%20One%20of%20the%20more%20common%20approaches%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bmilitary%20sleep%20method%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20relies%20on%20breathwork%20and%20relaxation%20techniques%2C%20isn't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC6879759%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebacked%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20much%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-for-getting-better-sleep-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvice%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20building%20a%20regular%20sleep%20schedule%2C%20breathing%20filtered%20air%2C%20and%20getting%20daily%20exercise%2C%20will%20probably%20help%20you%20sleep%20better.%20But%20these%20individual%20hacks%20tend%20to%20distract%20from%20what's%20actually%20plaguing%20the%20most%20sleep-deprived%20Americans.%20If%20you%20lose%20your%20job%20or%20suffer%20from%20chronic%20pain%2C%20trying%20not%20to%20think%20for%2010%20seconds%20isn't%20going%20to%20do%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBig%2C%20structural%20changes%20such%20as%20better%20access%20to%20affordable%20healthcare%2C%20expanding%20income-support%20programs%20like%20the%20child%20tax%20credit%2C%20and%20implementing%20mental-health%20programs%20in%20schools%20would%20go%20a%20long%20way%20to%20ending%20the%20sleep-deprivation%20doom%20loop.%20But%20in%20the%20meantime%2C%20there%20are%20a%20few%20smaller%20fixes%2C%20such%20as%20moving%20school%20start%20times%20to%208%3A30%20a.m.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20the%20most%20sleep-deprived%20states%2C%20schools%20tend%20to%20start%20earlier%2C%20beginning%20at%207%3A40%20a.m.%20on%20average%20in%20Mississippi%20and%207%3A49%20a.m.%20in%20Alabama.%20Students%20slog%20through%20school%20in%20a%20fog%20of%20sleep%20deprivation%2C%20which%20affects%20their%20ability%20to%20learn.%20Pushing%20back%20start%20times%20can%20improve%20grades%20by%204.5%25%2C%20or%20the%20equivalent%20of%20three%20months%20of%20student%20learning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20CDC%2C%2070%25%20of%20high%20schoolers%20are%20not%20getting%20enough%20sleep.%20One%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rand.org%2Fpubs%2Fresearch_reports%2FRR2109.html%3Fadbsc%3Dsocial_20170831_1772051%26adbid%3D903257824167313410%26adbpl%3Dtw%26adbpr%3D22545453%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20delaying%20school%20start%20times%20to%208%3A30%20a.m.%20or%20later%20for%20high%20schools%20and%20elementary%20schools%20would%20add%20%2483%20billion%20to%20the%20US%20economy%20within%20a%20decade%20because%20of%20students'%20improved%20performance%20in%20school.%20California%20and%20Florida%20are%20already%20on%20board%2C%20recently%20passing%20bills%20mandating%20that%20all%20public%20high%20schools%20start%20no%20earlier%20than%208%3A30%20a.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20way%20forward%20is%20through%20labor%20regulations.%20In%202003%2C%20the%20Accreditation%20Council%20for%20Graduate%20Medical%20Education%20implemented%20rules%20limiting%20work%20hours%20for%20all%20medical%20residents%20to%20ensure%20they%20got%20enough%20sleep.%20Since%20then%2C%20care%20for%20patients%20and%20doctors'%20well-being%20have%20improved.%20But%20more%20rules%20are%20needed%20%E2%80%94%2040%25%20of%20healthcare%20workers%20still%20weren't%20getting%20enough%20sleep%20when%20the%20CDC%20last%20looked%20at%20the%20issue%2C%20in%202017.%20Industries%20such%20as%20transportation%20also%20have%20rules%20to%20protect%20sleep%2C%20limiting%20truck%20drivers%20to%2011%20hours%20on%20the%20road%20at%20a%20time.%20But%20there%20are%20many%20professions%20where%20people%20are%20left%20to%20their%20own%20devices.%20In%20the%20food-services%20industry%2C%20people%20juggle%20inconsistent%20shifts%20and%20low%20pay%20that%20often%20requires%20taking%20on%20multiple%20jobs%2C%20and%2040%25%20of%20workers%20don't%20get%20enough%20sleep.%20Among%20gig%20workers%2C%20who%20lack%20traditional%20employment%20protections%2C%20inconsistent%20pay%20has%20been%20found%20to%20contribute%20to%20worse%20sleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20people%20start%20to%20fall%20behind%20on%20sleep%2C%20their%20social%2C%20economic%2C%20and%20physical%20lives%20soon%20begin%20to%20suffer.%20The%20cycles%20of%20inequality%20deepen%2C%20and%20no%20amount%20of%20red-light%20therapy%20can%20reverse%20the%20trend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjeremy-ney%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJeremy%20Ney%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20the%20author%20of%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Famericaninequality.substack.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmerican%20Inequality%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20data%20publication%20project%20that%20spotlights%20US%20inequality%20topics.%20He%20was%20previously%20a%20macro%20policy%20strategist%2