s%20(NRAO)%20Very%20Long%20Baseline%20Array%20(VLBA)%C2%A0detected%20%E2%80%9C16%20supermassive%20black%20holes%20in%20galaxies%20surrounded%20by%20hot%20gas%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F8Q2-H4ulQc4%3Fsi%3DauMKukojibGqrRQP%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsing%20radio%20data%20from%20the%20VLBA%2C%20operated%20by%20the%20National%20Radio%20Astronomical%20Observatory%2C%20they%20studied%20the%20directions%20of%20beams%20%E2%80%94%20also%20known%20as%20jets%20%E2%80%94%20of%20particles%20fired%20a%20few%20light-years%20away%20from%20the%20black%20holes%2C%20the%20space%20agency%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20gives%20the%20scientists%20a%20picture%20of%20where%20each%20beam%20is%20currently%20pointed%2C%20as%20seen%20from%20Earth.%20Each%20black%20hole%20fires%20two%20beams%20in%20opposite%20directions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrancesco%20Ubertosi%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Bologna%20in%20Italy%2C%20who%20led%20the%20study%2C%20said%20that%20they%20found%20about%20a%20third%20of%20the%20beams%20were%20now%20pointing%20in%20completely%20different%20directions%20than%20before.%20These%20Death%20Star%20black%20holes%20are%20%26quot%3Bswivelling%20around%20and%20pointing%20at%20new%20targets%2C%26quot%3B%20like%20the%20fictional%20space%20station%20in%20Star%20Wars%2C%20Mr%20Ubertosi%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20X-ray%20and%20radio%20data%20suggest%20that%20the%20jets%20can%20change%20directions%20over%2090%20degrees%20in%20some%20cases%20and%20more%20timescales%20between%20one%20million%20years%20and%20a%20few%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECo-author%20Gerrit%20Schellenberger%20of%20the%20Center%20For%20Astrophysics%20(CFA)%20noted%20that%20these%20black%20holes%20are%20likely%20more%20than%2010%20billion%20years%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Gerrit%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20consider%20a%20large%20change%20in%20direction%20over%20a%20few%20million%20years%20to%20be%20fast.%20Changing%20the%20direction%20of%20the%20giant%20black%20hole%20beams%20in%20about%20a%20million%20years%20is%20analogous%20to%20changing%20the%20direction%20of%20a%20new%20battleship%20in%20a%20few%20minutes.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20after%20this%20discovery%2C%20the%20scientists%20believe%20that%20the%20beams%20from%20the%20black%20holes%20play%20an%20important%20role%20in%20determining%20how%20many%20stars%20form%20in%20their%20galaxies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20beams%20change%20directions%20by%20large%20amounts%2C%20they%20can%20tamp%20down%20star%20formation%20across%20much%20larger%20areas%20of%20the%20galaxy%2C%E2%80%9D%20added%20NASA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20galaxies%20are%20too%20distant%20to%20tell%20if%20the%20beams%20from%20the%20Death%20Star%20black%20holes%20are%20damaging%20stars%20and%20their%20planets%2C%20but%20we%20are%20confident%20they%20are%20preventing%20many%20stars%20and%20planets%20from%20forming%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%20co-author%20Ewan%20O'Sullivan%2C%20also%20from%20CFA%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717053240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fdd6dt61_black-hole_625x300_30_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasa-discovers-death-star-black-hole-that-fires-powerful-beam-at-planets-5777453%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20team%20of%20National%20Aeronautics%20and%20Space%20Administration%20(NASA)%20scientists%20has%20discovered%20vast%20black%20holes%20that%20are%20%26quot%3Bfiring%20powerful%20beams%20of%20particles%20into%20space%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasa-discovers-death-star-black-hole-that-fires-powerful-bea